---
import Layout from '../../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const title = "UAE Work Visa Insurance Guide 2026 | Employment Visa Requirements";
const description = "Complete guide to UAE work visa insurance requirements. Covers Employment Visa, Golden Visa, health insurance mandates, and expat coverage options for working in Dubai and Abu Dhabi.";

const tocItems = [
  { id: "overview", label: "Overview" },
  { id: "quick-decision", label: "Is This Right for You?" },
  { id: "official-requirements", label: "Official Requirements" },
  { id: "insurance-requirements", label: "Insurance Requirements" },
  { id: "recommended-providers", label: "Recommended Providers" },
  { id: "costs", label: "Costs Breakdown" },
  { id: "application-timeline", label: "Application Timeline" },
  { id: "scenarios", label: "Real-World Scenarios" },
  { id: "common-mistakes", label: "Common Mistakes" },
  { id: "healthcare-access", label: "Healthcare Access" },
  { id: "faq", label: "FAQs" },
  { id: "verdict", label: "Final Verdict" }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <PageShell
    title="UAE Work Visa Insurance Guide"
    subtitle="Your complete guide to working legally in the UAE with proper health coverage"
    heroImage="/images/countries/uae-hero-bg.png"
    tocItems={tocItems}
  >
    <!-- Quick Facts Box -->
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-4">Quick Facts: UAE Work Visa</h3>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-sm">
        <div><strong>Visa Type:</strong> Employment Visa (sponsored)</div>
        <div><strong>Initial Duration:</strong> 2-3 years (renewable)</div>
        <div><strong>Income Tax:</strong> 0% personal income tax</div>
        <div><strong>Processing Time:</strong> 2-4 weeks</div>
        <div><strong>Health Insurance:</strong> Mandatory (employer-provided)</div>
        <div><strong>PR Pathway:</strong> Golden Visa (10 years) for high earners</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Overview -->
    <section id="overview" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Overview</h2>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        The UAE Employment Visa is your gateway to working in one of the world's most dynamic economies. Unlike many countries, the UAE operates on an employer sponsorship system where your visa is directly tied to your employer. Dubai and Abu Dhabi have mandatory health insurance requirements, making coverage non-negotiable for legal employment.
      </p>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        With zero personal income tax, tax-free salaries attract professionals from around the world. The introduction of the Golden Visa in 2019 has also created pathways to long-term residency for high earners, investors, and specialized talent without requiring employer sponsorship.
      </p>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        The UAE healthcare system is world-class but expensive. Private hospitals dominate, and even basic consultations can cost AED 300-800 ($80-220). Your employer is legally required to provide health insurance, but coverage levels vary significantly. Understanding what's included—and what gaps you might need to fill—is essential before relocating.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Quick Decision Guide -->
    <section id="quick-decision" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Is the UAE Work Visa Right for You?</h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3">Good Fit If You...</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-green-800">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Have a job offer from a UAE-registered company</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Want to maximize earnings with 0% income tax</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Work in finance, tech, healthcare, or construction</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Are comfortable with employer-sponsored visa systems</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-green-600 mt-1">✓</span>
              <span>Earn AED 30,000+/month (for Golden Visa eligibility)</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-3">Consider Alternatives If...</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-amber-800">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600 mt-1">→</span>
              <span>You want visa independence from your employer</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600 mt-1">→</span>
              <span>You have pre-existing conditions (limited coverage)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600 mt-1">→</span>
              <span>You're a freelancer (Freelance Visa is separate)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600 mt-1">→</span>
              <span>You need guaranteed permanent residency pathway</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
              <span class="text-amber-600 mt-1">→</span>
              <span>You prefer public healthcare systems</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Official Requirements -->
    <section id="official-requirements" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Official Requirements</h2>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">Eligibility Criteria</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Requirement", "Details", "Notes"]}
        rows={[
          ["Job Offer", "Must have offer from UAE-registered company", "Free zone or mainland"],
          ["Entry Permit", "Employer applies before arrival", "Valid 60 days to enter"],
          ["Medical Test", "HIV, TB, Hepatitis B/C screening", "Must pass for visa issuance"],
          ["Emirates ID", "Biometric ID card required", "Applied with visa"],
          ["Minimum Salary", "Varies by role/emirate", "Some free zones have minimums"],
          ["Education", "Attested degree for skilled roles", "UAE embassy attestation required"]
        ]}
      />

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">Required Documents</h3>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Valid passport</strong> – Minimum 6 months validity, clean pages</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Passport photos</strong> – White background, recent</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Employment contract</strong> – Signed by both parties</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Attested degree</strong> – Home country + UAE embassy attestation</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Medical fitness certificate</strong> – From approved UAE clinic</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
            <span class="text-primary-600 mt-1">•</span>
            <span><strong>Entry permit</strong> – Provided by employer</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">Visa Categories</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Visa Type", "Duration", "Requirements", "Best For"]}
        rows={[
          ["Standard Employment", "2 years", "Job offer + sponsorship", "Most employees"],
          ["Green Visa", "5 years", "Skilled worker + AED 15,000/month", "Self-sponsored professionals"],
          ["Golden Visa", "10 years", "AED 30,000/month OR specialized talent", "High earners, executives"],
          ["Free Zone Employment", "1-3 years", "Free zone company sponsor", "Tech, media workers"]
        ]}
      />
    </section>

    <!-- Insurance Requirements -->
    <section id="insurance-requirements" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Insurance Requirements</h2>

      <div class="bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg p-4 mb-6">
        <p class="text-red-800 font-medium">⚠️ Health Insurance is Mandatory</p>
        <p class="text-red-700 text-sm mt-1">Dubai and Abu Dhabi require all residents to have health insurance. Employers must provide coverage for employees. Working without valid insurance is illegal and can result in fines up to AED 500/day.</p>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">Mandatory Coverage (Dubai/Abu Dhabi)</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Coverage", "Dubai Minimum", "Abu Dhabi Minimum"]}
        rows={[
          ["Annual Limit", "AED 150,000", "AED 250,000"],
          ["Outpatient Care", "Required", "Required"],
          ["Inpatient Care", "Required", "Required"],
          ["Emergency", "Required", "Required"],
          ["Maternity", "Varies by plan", "Required for women"],
          ["Pre-existing Conditions", "6-month waiting period allowed", "12-month waiting period allowed"]
        ]}
      />

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">What Employers Typically Provide</h3>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        Most employers provide DHA (Dubai Health Authority) or HAAD (Abu Dhabi) compliant plans. Coverage quality varies dramatically based on your salary level and company policy. Senior employees often receive enhanced plans with AED 500,000+ coverage, while junior staff may get basic minimum plans.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 mb-6">
        <p class="text-amber-800 font-medium">Common Gaps in Employer Plans</p>
        <ul class="text-amber-700 text-sm mt-2 space-y-1">
          <li>• Dental and vision (usually excluded or limited)</li>
          <li>• Mental health coverage (often excluded entirely)</li>
          <li>• Coverage outside UAE (emergency only, if at all)</li>
          <li>• Pre-existing conditions (waiting periods or exclusions)</li>
          <li>• Alternative therapies (physiotherapy limits common)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">When You Need Additional Coverage</h3>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        Consider supplemental international health insurance if your employer plan has low limits (under AED 500,000), excludes global coverage, or doesn't cover your family. Many expats also want evacuation coverage to return home for serious treatment.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Recommended Providers -->
    <section id="recommended-providers" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-6">
        Your employer will provide a local DHA/HAAD compliant plan. These international providers offer supplemental or enhanced coverage for expats wanting broader protection.
      </p>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Provider", "Best For", "UAE Coverage", "Annual Cost", "Key Features"]}
        rows={[
          ["Cigna Global", "Executives & families", "Extensive network", "$3,500-8,000", "Direct billing at premium hospitals"],
          ["Allianz Care", "Long-term expats", "All major hospitals", "$2,800-6,500", "Worldwide coverage included"],
          ["BUPA Global", "UK expats", "Strong Dubai network", "$3,200-7,500", "No lifetime limits"],
          ["Now Health", "Asia-Pacific focus", "Growing network", "$2,500-5,500", "Good value comprehensive plans"],
          ["SafetyWing", "Budget supplement", "Emergency only", "$600-1,200", "Pairs with employer basic plan"]
        ]}
      />

      <CTABox
        title="Compare International Health Plans for UAE"
        description="Get quotes from multiple providers. Find the right balance of coverage and cost for your UAE employment."
        buttonText="Compare Plans"
        buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
      />
    </section>

    <!-- Costs Breakdown -->
    <section id="costs" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Costs Breakdown</h2>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">Visa & Setup Costs</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Item", "Cost (AED)", "Cost (USD)", "Notes"]}
        rows={[
          ["Entry Permit", "1,000-2,000", "$270-545", "Usually employer pays"],
          ["Medical Test", "300-500", "$80-135", "DHA/HAAD approved clinic"],
          ["Emirates ID", "370", "$100", "3-year validity"],
          ["Visa Stamping", "500-1,000", "$135-270", "Residence visa"],
          ["Labor Card", "300", "$80", "MOHRE registration"],
          ["Degree Attestation", "1,500-3,000", "$400-815", "Home + UAE attestation"]
        ]}
      />

      <div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
        <p class="text-green-800 font-medium">Employer Typically Covers</p>
        <p class="text-green-700 text-sm mt-1">Most visa costs (entry permit, stamping, labor card) are employer-paid by UAE law. You're usually responsible for degree attestation in your home country before arrival.</p>
      </div>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">Health Insurance Costs</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Plan Type", "Annual Cost", "Who Pays", "Coverage Level"]}
        rows={[
          ["Basic Employer Plan", "AED 1,500-3,000", "Employer", "AED 150,000-250,000 limit"],
          ["Enhanced Employer Plan", "AED 5,000-15,000", "Employer", "AED 500,000-1,000,000 limit"],
          ["Supplemental International", "AED 2,000-5,000", "Employee", "Fills gaps in employer plan"],
          ["Full International Plan", "AED 10,000-30,000", "Employee", "Comprehensive global coverage"]
        ]}
      />

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">Living Costs (Monthly)</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Category", "Dubai", "Abu Dhabi", "Notes"]}
        rows={[
          ["Rent (1BR)", "AED 5,000-12,000", "AED 4,000-9,000", "Location dependent"],
          ["Utilities", "AED 500-1,200", "AED 400-1,000", "AC is expensive"],
          ["Transport", "AED 400-800", "AED 400-700", "Metro/bus or fuel"],
          ["Food", "AED 2,000-4,000", "AED 1,800-3,500", "Mix of home/dining"],
          ["Healthcare (OOP)", "AED 200-500", "AED 200-500", "Co-pays, uncovered items"]
        ]}
      />
    </section>

    <!-- Application Timeline -->
    <section id="application-timeline" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Application Timeline</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-medium text-primary-600">Before Arrival</div>
          <div class="flex-grow border-l-2 border-primary-200 pl-4 pb-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Document Preparation</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Attest degree in home country. Gather passport photos, employment contract, and supporting documents. Complete any employer onboarding requirements.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-medium text-primary-600">Week 1</div>
          <div class="flex-grow border-l-2 border-primary-200 pl-4 pb-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Entry Permit & Arrival</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Employer applies for entry permit. You receive visa via email. Arrive in UAE within 60 days. Entry permit stamped on arrival.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-medium text-primary-600">Week 2</div>
          <div class="flex-grow border-l-2 border-primary-200 pl-4 pb-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Medical Examination</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Complete medical fitness test at approved clinic. Blood test, chest X-ray. Results typically in 2-3 days. Required for visa stamping.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-medium text-primary-600">Week 2-3</div>
          <div class="flex-grow border-l-2 border-primary-200 pl-4 pb-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Emirates ID Application</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Biometrics appointment at Emirates ID center. Photo and fingerprints taken. Card delivered to home address in 5-10 days.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-medium text-primary-600">Week 3-4</div>
          <div class="flex-grow border-l-2 border-primary-200 pl-4 pb-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Residence Visa Stamping</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Passport submitted for visa stamp. Takes 3-5 working days. Now legal to work and reside in UAE.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-24 text-sm font-medium text-primary-600">Week 4</div>
          <div class="flex-grow border-l-2 border-primary-200 pl-4">
            <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Health Insurance Activation</h4>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm">Employer provides health insurance card. Register on DHA app (Dubai) or Thiqa system (Abu Dhabi). Coverage now active.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Real-World Scenarios -->
    <section id="scenarios" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Finance Professional to Dubai</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">James, 32, moves from London for a banking role in DIFC. Salary AED 45,000/month. Employer provides enhanced insurance (AED 1M limit). Visa processed in 3 weeks through DIFC Authority fast-track.</p>
          <p class="text-green-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: Smooth process, comprehensive coverage, Golden Visa eligible</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Teacher in Abu Dhabi</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">Sarah, 28, joins an international school. Salary AED 15,000/month. Basic Thiqa insurance provided. Discovers dental and home country visits aren't covered. Adds supplemental plan for AED 3,000/year.</p>
          <p class="text-amber-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: Needed supplemental insurance for adequate coverage</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Construction Engineer from India</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">Raj, 35, works for major contractor. Employer handles all visa costs. Medical test clears quickly. Basic insurance provided. Sends remittances home easily with zero tax on salary.</p>
          <p class="text-green-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: Straightforward process, tax-free income maximized</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Tech Worker with Pre-existing Condition</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">Lisa, 40, has Type 2 diabetes. Moves to Dubai for tech role. Employer insurance has 12-month waiting period for pre-existing conditions. Must pay for medication out-of-pocket initially (~AED 400/month).</p>
          <p class="text-amber-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: Coverage gap for first year, plan ahead for medication costs</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Family Relocation</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">Mohammed, 38, brings wife and two children. Salary AED 35,000/month exceeds family sponsorship minimum. Employer covers his insurance only. Must pay AED 8,000/year for family coverage.</p>
          <p class="text-amber-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: Additional costs for dependent insurance not covered by employer</p>
        </div>

        <div class="border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Failed Medical Exam</h4>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 text-sm mb-2">Chen, 29, tests positive for Hepatitis B during mandatory medical. Visa application rejected despite job offer. Must explore treatment or appeal options. Loses job opportunity.</p>
          <p class="text-red-700 text-sm font-medium">Outcome: Visa denied due to medical results—screening is strict</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Common Mistakes -->
    <section id="common-mistakes" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>

      <div class="space-y-4">
        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-400 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900">1. Not Attesting Degrees Before Arrival</h4>
          <p class="text-red-800 text-sm">Degree attestation must be done in your home country first (apostille or embassy attestation), then completed in UAE. This takes 2-4 weeks and can't be skipped. Arriving without attested documents delays your visa significantly.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-400 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900">2. Assuming Employer Insurance is Comprehensive</h4>
          <p class="text-red-800 text-sm">Basic employer plans meet legal minimums but often exclude dental, mental health, global coverage, and have low limits. Review your policy details carefully. AED 150,000 limit can be exhausted by one hospital stay.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-400 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900">3. Not Planning for Pre-existing Conditions</h4>
          <p class="text-red-800 text-sm">UAE insurance commonly has 6-12 month waiting periods for pre-existing conditions. Bring sufficient medication supply and budget for out-of-pocket costs during the waiting period.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-400 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900">4. Forgetting Family Insurance Costs</h4>
          <p class="text-red-800 text-sm">Employers typically only cover the employee's insurance. Dependent coverage (spouse, children) is usually your responsibility. Budget AED 3,000-10,000 per year per family member for adequate coverage.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-50 border-l-4 border-red-400 p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900">5. Working Before Visa is Complete</h4>
          <p class="text-red-800 text-sm">You cannot legally work until your residence visa is stamped in your passport and labor card is issued. Working on a visit visa or entry permit is illegal and can result in fines, deportation, and employment bans.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Healthcare Access -->
    <section id="healthcare-access" class="mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Healthcare System Access</h2>

      <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
        The UAE has a modern, private-dominated healthcare system. Quality is high but so are costs. Most care happens in private hospitals and clinics. Public facilities exist but are primarily for UAE nationals and low-income workers.
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">Healthcare Landscape</h3>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={["Aspect", "Dubai", "Abu Dhabi", "Other Emirates"]}
        rows={[
          ["Insurance Mandate", "DHA mandatory", "HAAD/Daman mandatory", "Varies (often none)"],
          ["Hospital Quality", "World-class private", "World-class private", "Good private options"],
          ["Typical Costs", "Highest in UAE", "High", "Lower"],
          ["Network Size", "Extensive", "Extensive", "More limited"],
          ["English Availability", "Universal", "Universal", "Very common"]
        ]}
      />

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mt-6 mb-3">Major Hospital Networks</h3>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Dubai</h4>
          <ul class="text-neutral-600 text-sm space-y-1">
            <li>• Mediclinic City Hospital</li>
            <li>• American Hospital Dubai</li>
            <li>• King's College Hospital</li>
            <li>• Saudi German Hospital</li>
